        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 7:44AM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 743 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Palestine to near Centerville to near
Franklin. Movement was southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
College Station, Bryan, northwestern Huntsville, Crockett,
Madisonville, Austonio, Trinity, Grapeland, Lovelady, Bedias, Kurten,
Latexo, Wixon Valley, Kyle Field, Bryan Utilities Lake, Normangee,
Iola, Crabbs Prairie, Mound City, and Pennington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
